-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Almarai and Saudi Hollandi Bank Advance
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2011-12-21T13:19:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/persian-gulf-stocks-almarai-and-saudi-hollandi-bank-advance.html
Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share
Index (SASEIDX)  advanced 0.7 percent to 6,330.01, the highest since Aug.
3, at the 3:30 p.m. close in Riyadh. The measure rose 1.5
percent this week. Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  slumped 1.8
percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Almarai Co. (ALMARAI)   climbed to the highest in 10
months, increasing 3.1 percent to 99.75 riyals. Saudi Arabia’s
largest food producer by market value acquired Fondomonte SA for
312 million riyals ($83 million).  Saudi Hollandi Bank (AAAL)   advanced to the highest since
Aug. 3, rising 3.2 percent to 28.8 riyals. The Saudi lender
plans to give one bonus share for every five held.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
